The Kepler-468 Exoplanetary System


Overview

Kepler-468 is a star with 0.96 times the mass of the Sun, and 0.87 times its radius. It is located NaN light years away from the solar system and is estimated to be 2 billion years old, as compared to the Sun which is roughly 4.6 billion years old.

Kepler-468 is known to have undefined exoplanets in orbit around it.


Exoplanets in the Kepler-468 system


Kepler-468 b

Kepler-468 b was discovered by the undefined observatory using the transit method. Its semi-major axis is 0.22 astronomical units, as compared to Earth's which is 1 astronomical unit. The radius of Kepler-468 b is 13.34 that of Earth.
